A vintage-style illustration of an ancient cartographer's workspace, featuring a large parchment scroll unfurling across a wooden desk, revealing an intricate nested map where smaller detailed maps are embedded within larger regional maps like Russian nesting dolls. Antique brass compasses, ink wells with quill pens, and worn leather-bound journals surround the central scroll. Warm candlelight casts amber shadows across the weathered wood grain and yellowed paper. The nested map structure shows interconnected territories flowing into one another organically, with delicate hand-drawn lines connecting related regions. Sepia tones dominate with touches of faded burgundy and forest green ink. Dust particles float in the candlelight, and a magnifying glass rests on one corner, revealing even finer detail within the nested structures.
